# C# / Blish HUD conventions

## Style

- Match existing code: `sealed` classes, nullable enabled, minimal scope, no over-abstraction.
- Namespace: `Ghost.Gw2EventTracker`, `Ghost.Gw2EventTracker.Services`, `Ghost.Gw2EventTracker.UI`, `Ghost.Gw2EventTracker.Models`.
- Module entry: `[Export(typeof(Module))]` on `EventTrackerModule`, MEF constructor with `[Import("ModuleParameters")]`.

## Blish UI

- Prefer `Panel` with `CanScroll = true` over `Container` (no scroll support).
- `ContentRegion.Size` is a `Point` — use `.X` / `.Y`, not `.Width`.
- Set child `Height` before parents that read layout in `OnResized`; guard null children during ctor.
- Textures from `ContentsManager.GetTexture("textures/...")` for custom module UI, or `AsyncTexture2D.FromAssetId(...)` / `ModuleTextures` for GW2 dat icons.

## Logging

```csharp
private static readonly Logger Logger = Logger.GetLogger<MyClass>();
```

## File encoding (critical)

`StrReplace` / `Write` can save `.cs` files as UTF-16 and break the build (`\0` errors). After editing `.cs` files, if build fails with encoding errors, re-save as UTF-8 without BOM:

```powershell
$utf8 = New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false
$text = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllText($path, [System.Text.Encoding]::Unicode)
[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText($path, $text, $utf8)
```

Same for `manifest.json` — always UTF-8 without BOM.
